  "description": "<i>Chinese Chess</i> is 2D board turn-based strategy game, based on XiangQi - The chinese version of chess with different rules. The player controls an army of figures (general, advisor, elephant, horse etc. - each has their own move and attack rules) and tries to defeat the enemy's army by capturing the enemy's general. The battlefield is a 10x9 grid board with a special arena (river and palaces). This game has several views  -  traditional 2D and isometric with real figures (2 sets).",
